WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.680
Mother Teresa by Darcy Adrian Valance

00:05.730 --> 00:09.500
Penguin readers level one, there are a lot of good

00:09.500 --> 00:12.180
people in the world, but not many

00:12.180 --> 00:17.160
of them are world famous. Mother Teresa was a small

00:17.160 --> 00:21.880
quiet nun. She died in 1997 in India,

00:21.880 --> 00:27.540
but people in many countries remember her. They talk about

00:27.540 --> 00:30.360
her and they love her. Why?

00:31.120 --> 00:38.460
Read her story. The answer is here. Agnes Gonsha

00:39.960 --> 00:44.940
For her 13 years, her name was not Teresa. It

00:44.940 --> 00:49.140
was Agnes. Her family name was Boyaggio.

00:50.440 --> 00:54.120
There were two children in the family before her, a

00:54.120 --> 00:58.580
boy and a girl. Then little Agnes Gonsha

00:58.580 --> 01:02.240
came into the world on the 26th of August 1910.

01:04.920 --> 01:07.080
Her mother and father were from Albania,

01:07.780 --> 01:12.060
but they lived in the town of Scopia. At that

01:12.060 --> 01:17.020
time Scopia was in Serbia. They had a good home

01:17.020 --> 01:21.920
because her father did well in his work. Then her

01:21.920 --> 01:25.480
father suddenly died. Agnes was only

01:25.480 --> 01:29.680
eight years old. Her sister was 14 and her brother

01:29.680 --> 01:33.560
was 11. Things were difficult for Agnes's

01:33.560 --> 01:38.280
mother, but she was strong for her children. She worked

01:38.280 --> 01:41.220
and did well. She loved the children

01:41.220 --> 01:46.040
and they had a happy home. There were some poor

01:46.040 --> 01:49.420
people near their home. These people did not

01:49.420 --> 01:53.100
have much money for food and Agnes's mother was good

01:53.100 --> 01:57.020
to them too. She was a Christian, a Catholic

01:57.020 --> 02:02.440
and God was very important to her. She prayed to

02:02.440 --> 02:05.280
God every evening with her children and they

02:05.280 --> 02:10.400
all went to church every week. At the church there

02:10.400 --> 02:12.640
were stories about Christian missionaries in

02:12.640 --> 02:17.640
India and poor African countries. These people lived for God.

02:18.680 --> 02:20.240
They went to India and Africa

02:20.240 --> 02:23.740
because they wanted to bring God's love to poor people

02:23.740 --> 02:27.140
there. Some of the missionaries in India

02:27.140 --> 02:32.000
were men from Scopia. Agnes loved hearing about the work

02:32.000 --> 02:34.560
of these missionaries. She started to

02:34.560 --> 02:38.780
think, what am I going to do for God? She

02:38.780 --> 02:43.160
wanted to live for God, but how? Did she want

02:43.160 --> 02:43.560
to be a

02:43.560 --> 02:48.380
nun? Did she want to live only for God? She

02:48.380 --> 02:54.000
prayed for answers. After five years the answer came to

02:54.000 --> 02:58.660
her. She wanted to live only for him. She wanted

02:58.660 --> 03:03.100
to be a nun in India. Her mother was very

03:03.100 --> 03:03.460
unhappy

03:03.460 --> 03:07.060
about this. She loved her daughter and did not want

03:07.060 --> 03:10.480
to say goodbye to her. She went to her bedroom

03:10.480 --> 03:15.040
and stayed there all day. But after a day and

03:15.040 --> 03:19.020
a night she came out and said to Agnes, put

03:19.020 --> 03:19.320
your

03:19.320 --> 03:24.500
hand in his hand and walk with him. On the

03:24.500 --> 03:29.760
25th of September 1928 Agnes said goodbye to her friends

03:29.760 --> 03:34.340
and her home in Scopia. At the station she said

03:34.340 --> 03:39.320
goodbye to her family. She was 18 years old and

03:39.320 --> 03:39.500
she

03:39.500 --> 03:45.360
did not see her mother or her sister again. To

03:45.360 --> 03:49.520
India. She went by train and boat to Ireland.

03:50.720 --> 03:52.900
There she went to the home of the Loreto nuns.

03:54.100 --> 03:57.320
She wanted to be a Loreto nun because many of

03:57.320 --> 03:57.480
them

03:57.480 --> 04:02.940
worked in India. Agnes stayed with the nuns at Loreto

04:02.940 --> 04:04.860
house in Dublin for six weeks.

04:05.900 --> 04:10.640
Then she was on a boat again to India. She

04:10.640 --> 04:12.120
was now sister Teresa.

04:13.900 --> 04:17.540
These days you can get from Ireland to India very

04:17.540 --> 04:21.440
quickly, but in those days people were on the boat

04:21.440 --> 04:26.560
for seven weeks. It went from Ireland to Spain then

04:26.560 --> 04:29.300
across the Mediterranean Sea to Suez in Egypt

04:29.860 --> 04:33.220
down the Red Sea across the Arabian Sea to Sri

04:33.220 --> 04:36.100
Lanka and then up to Calcutta in India.

04:37.520 --> 04:43.400
From Calcutta she went by train to Darjeeling. Calcutta was

04:43.400 --> 04:45.200
a big place with a lot of noise

04:46.080 --> 04:52.760
but Darjeeling was quiet and beautiful. Young sister Teresa did

04:52.760 --> 04:53.800
not know much English

04:54.440 --> 04:59.160
but she was a good student. She was friendly too

04:59.160 --> 05:03.440
and she often smiled. She was very happy there.

05:04.880 --> 05:09.160
After two years her English was good and she started

05:09.160 --> 05:11.640
to teach children in the nuns school.

05:13.440 --> 05:16.100
Then she moved to one of the Loreto nuns schools

05:16.100 --> 05:17.120
in Calcutta.

05:18.260 --> 05:22.560
Its name was Loreto Antali, a big school for girls.

05:23.740 --> 05:26.180
Many of the girls were from poor families.

05:28.200 --> 05:31.920
The school day started early in the morning but the

05:31.920 --> 05:35.640
nuns day started before that. Every morning

05:35.640 --> 05:39.400
the nuns prayed for a long time. Then they worked

05:39.400 --> 05:41.380
in the school in the morning and the afternoon.

05:42.320 --> 05:45.720
They worked in the evening too because many of the

05:45.720 --> 05:49.420
girls lived at the school. After a long day

05:49.980 --> 05:54.320
they prayed again and then went to bed. The nuns

05:54.320 --> 05:58.060
did not have holidays. They did not listen to music

05:58.060 --> 06:03.420
or go shopping. They did not see their families but

06:03.420 --> 06:05.860
they were happy because they lived for God.

06:06.880 --> 06:10.000
They were happy and strong all day because they remembered

06:10.000 --> 06:11.840
his love every morning.

06:14.040 --> 06:17.880
Sister Teresa liked teaching and she was good at it.

06:18.720 --> 06:21.960
She was a teacher at Loreto Antali for 12 years

06:22.480 --> 06:27.300
and then from 1944 she was the head teacher for

06:27.300 --> 06:28.040
four years.

06:30.680 --> 06:32.080
The Streets of Calcutta

06:33.400 --> 06:40.400
Calcutta or Calcutta today has 15 million people. In the

06:40.400 --> 06:43.420
1940s it was a very big place too

06:43.840 --> 06:48.900
and many new people arrived every year. The people were

06:48.900 --> 06:50.140
Hindus, Muslims,

06:50.140 --> 06:58.060
Christians, Sikhs and Buddhists. Calcutta had beautiful buildings, big hotels,

06:58.740 --> 06:59.960
offices, banks

06:59.960 --> 07:06.020
and houses. Many writers and famous people lived there but

07:06.020 --> 07:07.840
Calcutta had some big problems.

07:08.820 --> 07:12.260
A lot of people were very poor. They did not

07:12.260 --> 07:14.860
have any money and they lived in slons,

07:15.380 --> 07:20.420
bad places with bad houses. Many people did not have

07:20.420 --> 07:23.200
a home. They lived and died in the streets.

07:24.920 --> 07:29.560
The years 1943 to 46 were very bad years for

07:29.560 --> 07:33.700
Calcutta. There was not much food and it was very

07:33.700 --> 07:38.740
expensive. Poor families did not have money for this expensive

07:38.740 --> 07:41.540
food and in those three years

07:41.540 --> 07:46.880
about three million people died. Every day there were dead

07:46.880 --> 07:47.900
people in the streets.

07:49.520 --> 07:52.580
Mother Teresa wanted to help the poor people in the

07:52.580 --> 07:55.420
slums but this was difficult for her.

07:56.260 --> 07:59.020
She was a nun and nuns did not often go

07:59.020 --> 08:03.100
out into the streets. Many nuns helped poor people in

08:03.100 --> 08:08.320
schools, big food kitchens and hospitals but nuns did not

08:08.320 --> 08:10.660
usually go out to poor people in slums.

08:12.740 --> 08:15.660
She prayed to God for an answer to her problem.

08:17.120 --> 08:21.160
On the 10th of September 1946 she was on a

08:21.160 --> 08:21.440
train

08:21.440 --> 08:25.400
from Calcutta to Darjeeling and the answer came to her.

08:26.340 --> 08:29.700
The answer was go and work in the slums

08:29.700 --> 08:34.240
with the poor people. This was new work for a

08:34.240 --> 08:36.980
nun and the head of the Catholic Church in

08:36.980 --> 08:41.680
Calcutta said wait. He wanted to think about it first.

08:42.980 --> 08:45.220
Mother Teresa wanted to start quickly

08:45.880 --> 08:51.340
but she waited two years. Then in August 1948 a

08:51.340 --> 08:55.100
letter came from him. He was happy about her new

08:55.100 --> 09:00.960
work. Loreto Antaly was her home and the nuns were

09:00.960 --> 09:04.880
her only friends but she said goodbye and moved

09:04.880 --> 09:10.200
into a small room near a slum. The blue and

09:10.200 --> 09:15.240
white sari. Indian women usually dress in saris.

09:16.400 --> 09:20.340
There are beautiful expensive saris and there are poor saris

09:20.340 --> 09:23.420
for poor women. Mother Teresa

09:23.420 --> 09:26.660
dressed in a poor blue and white sari because she

09:26.660 --> 09:28.840
wanted to work with very poor people.

09:30.240 --> 09:33.260
Today there are many nuns in these blue and white

09:33.260 --> 09:36.220
saris but on her first day in the slum

09:36.220 --> 09:41.900
mother Teresa was alone. She was only one small woman

09:41.900 --> 09:44.600
with no helpers and no money.

09:46.380 --> 09:50.740
How did she start her new work? First she prayed

09:50.740 --> 09:53.640
to God and then she walked into the slum.

09:54.520 --> 09:58.580
There she talked to poor children. Many of them lived

09:58.580 --> 10:01.300
in the street. They had no home,

10:01.960 --> 10:07.800
no family and no school. She started to teach them

10:07.800 --> 10:10.400
in the street. The children liked her

10:10.870 --> 10:13.720
and the day after that a lot of children came

10:13.720 --> 10:17.720
to her new school. Then they came every day.

10:18.920 --> 10:22.020
One day there was a poor old woman in the

10:22.020 --> 10:25.600
street. She did not have a home and she was

10:25.600 --> 10:26.340
very ill.

10:27.480 --> 10:30.500
The doctors in the hospital did not want her because

10:30.500 --> 10:33.880
she was poor and very old. She was a dying

10:33.880 --> 10:38.300
woman. She did not have a family. She was alone.

10:39.400 --> 10:41.560
People in the street did not want to go near

10:41.560 --> 10:41.840
her

10:42.920 --> 10:46.020
but mother Teresa went to her and talked to her.

10:46.840 --> 10:48.660
She washed the woman and stayed with her.

10:49.560 --> 10:54.000
The woman died but she did not die alone. She

10:54.000 --> 10:56.620
died with a friend with her hand in mother

10:56.620 --> 11:01.220
Teresa's hand. There were often dying people in those streets.

11:02.280 --> 11:03.900
Mother Teresa stayed with them

11:04.440 --> 11:09.280
and they did not die alone. Many poor street people

11:09.280 --> 11:10.460
did not have any food.

11:11.360 --> 11:15.720
Mother Teresa asked people for food for them. Some people

11:15.720 --> 11:18.660
helped her. Some people were angry

11:18.660 --> 11:23.760
and did not help. For two months Mother Teresa worked

11:23.760 --> 11:26.960
alone. It was a difficult time for her.

11:28.180 --> 11:31.480
Then two of her Indian students from Loretta and Tali

11:31.480 --> 11:33.120
came to her and worked with her.

11:34.060 --> 11:38.700
After two years there were 12 nuns with her. They

11:38.700 --> 11:41.580
all had blue and white saris and they had

11:41.580 --> 11:46.580
a name, the missionaries of charity. They worked in street

11:46.580 --> 11:48.960
schools and the open street clinics.

11:50.240 --> 11:53.720
These clinics were not hospitals but they were a big

11:53.720 --> 11:55.400
help for people in the slums.

11:57.080 --> 12:00.700
People in Calcutta started to talk about Mother Teresa and

12:00.700 --> 12:01.720
her missionaries of charity.

12:03.540 --> 12:06.300
Many people wanted to help her and to give money

12:06.300 --> 12:06.760
to her.

12:08.200 --> 12:12.440
In 1952 the government of Calcutta gave her a big

12:12.440 --> 12:15.580
building and she started a home for dying

12:15.580 --> 12:20.740
people there. After this the nuns started a big home

12:20.740 --> 12:24.480
for children. Many poor children in Calcutta

12:24.480 --> 12:27.460
did not have a home or a mother or father.

12:28.920 --> 12:31.580
At the nun's new children's home there was food

12:31.580 --> 12:36.360
and a bed for them and love too. For 10

12:36.360 --> 12:39.540
years Mother Teresa and her missionaries of charity

12:40.100 --> 12:44.720
worked only in Calcutta. Every year there were new nuns.

12:46.040 --> 12:48.760
After 10 years they started to work

12:48.760 --> 12:52.720
away from Calcutta too. They opened new homes for dying

12:52.720 --> 12:54.520
people, homes for children,

12:54.980 --> 12:59.740
schools, clinics and food kitchens in 23 places in India.

13:01.860 --> 13:06.580
A love letter to the world. There are poor people

13:06.580 --> 13:07.620
in every country.

13:08.600 --> 13:13.720
In 1965 the missionaries of charity started working in Venezuela,

13:14.380 --> 13:16.640
South America. After that

13:16.640 --> 13:20.620
they opened a home in Rome. Then they went to

13:20.620 --> 13:22.940
Tanzania and many countries in Africa,

13:23.320 --> 13:30.440
Europe and Asia. In 1969 there was a television program

13:30.440 --> 13:32.640
about Mother Teresa and her work.

13:33.500 --> 13:36.820
It was a BBC programme and it was on British

13:36.820 --> 13:41.300
TV first. After the programme many letters

13:41.300 --> 13:45.500
arrived for her. A lot of people wanted to work

13:45.500 --> 13:46.760
with her or give money.

13:48.480 --> 13:51.640
Then people in Europe, the US and Asia watch the

13:51.640 --> 13:55.000
programme. People in many countries wanted to

13:55.000 --> 14:02.000
help her. Suddenly Mother Teresa was world famous. She did

14:02.000 --> 14:11.280
not like being famous. The

14:11.280 --> 14:14.600
she often said and she is sending a love letter

14:14.600 --> 14:15.320
to the world.

14:16.980 --> 14:20.920
People often asked her about her work. One question was

14:21.880 --> 14:25.560
you are with ill people and dying people every day.

14:26.320 --> 14:28.940
Is it difficult? How do you do it?

14:30.140 --> 14:35.580
Her answer was I see God in every person. For

14:35.580 --> 14:39.140
Mother Teresa, love of God was the important thing.

14:39.820 --> 14:42.620
She wanted to give her love to God but we

14:42.620 --> 14:45.960
cannot see God. We can only see God in people.

14:46.760 --> 14:50.720
She loved poor people and dying people because she loved

14:50.720 --> 14:54.020
God in them. For her this was beautiful,

14:54.800 --> 15:01.880
not difficult. She was on television again in 1979 because

15:01.880 --> 15:03.780
the Nobel Peace Prize went to her.

15:04.740 --> 15:10.160
This famous prize was $150,000 in that year. A

15:10.160 --> 15:11.140
lot of money then.

15:12.220 --> 15:15.800
Every year the prize goes to an important worker for

15:15.800 --> 15:16.400
world peace.

15:17.760 --> 15:21.460
Many important people go to Oslo from many countries for

15:21.460 --> 15:22.160
the prize day.

15:22.900 --> 15:28.340
On that day in 1979, Mother Teresa talked to them

15:28.340 --> 15:32.100
about love and peace. They asked her,

15:32.740 --> 15:37.300
how can we get world peace? She answered, go home

15:37.300 --> 15:39.060
and love your family.

15:41.140 --> 15:45.280
In the 1980s there were missionaries of charity in a

15:45.280 --> 15:46.160
hundred countries.

15:47.300 --> 15:50.360
They were not only in poor countries. There was a

15:50.360 --> 15:52.540
home for dying people in New York too.

15:54.080 --> 15:57.300
Mother Teresa often talked to heads of government in these

15:57.300 --> 15:57.740
countries

15:58.520 --> 16:03.300
but she always dressed in her poor woman's sari. In

16:03.300 --> 16:07.980
1990, Mother Teresa was 80 years old but she

16:07.980 --> 16:12.020
did not start working. Her day started at four o

16:12.020 --> 16:15.060
'clock in the morning. She worked all day and

16:15.060 --> 16:21.140
into the night. She had little sleep. A light in

16:21.140 --> 16:25.920
a dark time. Mother Teresa died in September

16:27.100 --> 16:30.500
1997 at the home of the missionaries of charity in

16:30.500 --> 16:35.160
Calcutta. At that time there were 4,000 missionaries

16:35.160 --> 16:40.620
of charity in 123 countries and 3 million people worked

16:40.620 --> 16:44.800
with them. People wanted to see her and say

16:44.800 --> 16:49.440
goodbye to her. Poor people from Calcutta and people from

16:49.440 --> 16:50.920
the government of India came.

16:52.180 --> 16:57.540
Important people arrived from many countries. One person said about

16:57.540 --> 17:01.180
her. She was a light in a dark time.

17:03.060 --> 17:05.960
Mother Teresa was a light for the poor people of

17:05.960 --> 17:09.300
Calcutta but she is a light for all of us

17:09.300 --> 17:09.620
too

17:10.180 --> 17:11.920
in every country of the world.

